      "side": 1,
      "message": "tq doesn\u0027t care about the real clock.\n\nHowever, ctx.Deadline() can\u0027t be extended!\nSo, if cvtesting.Test.SetUp() put deadline at say 2021-07-11\nbut later testclock is moved to say 2022-mm-dd,\nthen ctx.Deadline() is still 2021-07-11!\n\nThus, when TQ checks whether it has time to enqueue task after the transaction,\nTQ decides it can\u0027t -- sweeper should do it instead.\n\nAnd this stuff is actually non-trivial to debug -- i had to add logging.Debugf(ctx, \"WTF\"...) statements inside TQ to figure it out, and this happened to 3 times since  December...",
      "parentUuid": "456b3e36_92309ea0",
